WEBVTT

1
00:03:17.343 --> 00:03:18.981
Stand up, guys-

2
00:03:19.779 --> 00:03:21.588
They are here now.

3
00:13:03.529 --> 00:13:07.841
God gave us hands,
so we have to work.

4
00:13:08.868 --> 00:13:12.907
Since we are here, we have to work.

5
00:13:13.005 --> 00:13:15.281
Everybody works 12 hours.

6
00:13:15.374 --> 00:13:19.413
Some do work that requires
physical strength.


7
00:13:19.511 --> 00:13:21.252
Some use their mind.

8
00:13:21.347 --> 00:13:26.387
Some work requires hands and feet,
some work requires brains.


9
00:13:26.485 --> 00:13:31.127
Some people have to use their muscles,
some use their pens.


10
00:13:32.091 --> 00:13:34.401
There are different systems.

11
00:13:34.493 --> 00:13:36.268
Some work on machines.

12
00:13:36.362 --> 00:13:39.935
I do different things.

13
00:13:40.032 --> 00:13:42.410
The machines have to be controlled,

14
00:13:42.501 --> 00:13:46.142
either by using a button or the brain.

15
00:13:46.238 --> 00:13:48.684
If I am supposed to move this,

16
00:13:48.974 --> 00:13:52.478
I need to use my brain
to control the movement.


17
00:13:52.578 --> 00:13:56.549
There, you push a button.
It has a computer system.


18
00:13:56.649 --> 00:13:59.289
But here,
I need to use strength and brains.


19
00:13:59.385 --> 00:14:02.423
Or I would break my hands and legs.

20
00:14:02.521 --> 00:14:07.493
This has 220 kilograms of Chemicals.

21
00:14:07.593 --> 00:14:10.574
This has 100 kilograms. 
That one has 60.

22
00:14:10.663 --> 00:14:14.406
Everything has different
systems and weights.


23
00:14:14.500 --> 00:14:16.480
That is how things are made.

24
00:14:16.568 --> 00:14:22.177
The color will be made
according to the order.


25
00:14:23.375 --> 00:14:26.948
Sixty, 50, 40, 35 kilograms.
Whatever is needed.


26
00:14:27.046 --> 00:14:31.256
100, 200, 220,
that's the amount you make in color.


27
00:14:31.350 --> 00:14:34.160
You make it to match the order.

28
00:21:10.382 --> 00:21:13.591
Working on the Wheel
pays 210 rupees per shift.


29
00:21:15.487 --> 00:21:19.731
From that I have to eat,
save and raise my family.


30
00:21:22.094 --> 00:21:26.873
When I think about
having to raise my kids with this money,


31
00:21:26.965 --> 00:21:32.381
I try saving 1,000, 1,500, 2,000 rupees.

32
00:21:32.471 --> 00:21:35.384
The mill doesn't run
every day of the month.


33
00:21:35.474 --> 00:21:41.390
Tell me, who has the strength
to work nonstop for 36-48 hours?


34
00:21:41.480 --> 00:21:47.590
You have to break and twist your body
to save a paisa or two.


35
00:22:16.648 --> 00:22:19.822
How would the wealthy know
the problems of the poor?


36
00:22:19.918 --> 00:22:23.991
What am I even doing here
when I have everything back home?


37
00:22:24.089 --> 00:22:26.535
But it is poverty

38
00:22:26.625 --> 00:22:31.074
that makes a poor man take loans
to come here to work.


39
00:22:32.197 --> 00:22:37.010
When I don't have the money to come here,
I borrow at ten percent interest.


40
00:22:37.669 --> 00:22:39.842
I earn by hard labor, sir.

41
00:22:39.938 --> 00:22:42.145
It's a 12-hour shift here.

42
00:22:43.508 --> 00:22:48.116
You come at 8:00 in the morning
and leave at 8:00 in the evening.


43
00:22:48.213 --> 00:22:52.559
Once back, I cook and eat.

44
00:22:52.651 --> 00:22:58.624
Then after an hour's break,
I come for a second shift at 9:00 p.m.


45
00:23:01.693 --> 00:23:03.604
There are no other options.

46
00:23:03.695 --> 00:23:05.072
But what is poverty anyway?

47
00:23:07.065 --> 00:23:09.102
Poverty is harassment, sir.

48
00:23:09.935 --> 00:23:15.476
One has to forsake one's kids,
wife and parents to come here.


49
00:23:18.076 --> 00:23:20.920
You can't do anything. 
There is no cure.

50
00:23:30.956 --> 00:23:35.701
Sir, let me tell you
that nobody is exploiting me.


51
00:23:35.794 --> 00:23:38.604
I have taken loans
to come here to work.

52
00:23:38.697 --> 00:23:43.271
For my own needs, to raise my kids.

53
00:23:43.568 --> 00:23:49.883
Exploitation would mean
that I am being forced to work here.


54
00:23:49.975 --> 00:23:51.682
Wouldn't it?

55
00:23:51.776 --> 00:23:54.120
I have come from far away.

56
00:23:54.212 --> 00:23:59.161
I have traveled 1,600 kilometers
so I can work here.


57
00:24:00.118 --> 00:24:01.597
Of my own free will.

58
00:24:01.686 --> 00:24:03.188
Nobody is pressuring me.

59
00:24:03.288 --> 00:24:07.930
We all come here in order to work,
as we're in debt.


60
00:24:09.594 --> 00:24:11.232
There are thousands like me.

61
00:24:12.130 --> 00:24:17.079
The train I travel in has four carriages,
but there's not an inch of free space.


62
00:24:17.168 --> 00:24:21.639
You can't sit down,
you have to stand for 36 hours.


63
00:24:21.740 --> 00:24:28.055
There is neither water nor food.
I carry roasted chickpeas.


64
00:24:28.146 --> 00:24:30.956
For 36 hours there is no food.

65
00:26:53.024 --> 00:26:56.130
The only money
I spend is on chewing tobacco.


66
00:26:56.861 --> 00:26:59.171
What other habit can I truly afford?

67
00:26:59.264 --> 00:27:02.211
I can't even afford a cigarette.

68
00:27:02.300 --> 00:27:06.009
A cigarette is five rupees or ten.
I can't afford it.


69
00:27:06.104 --> 00:27:09.813
A packet of chewing tobacco
is two rupees and lasts all day.


70
00:27:09.908 --> 00:27:13.253
Won't you need a buzz
if you work all day?

71
00:27:13.344 --> 00:27:16.188
Chewing tobacco gives you relief.

72
00:27:16.281 --> 00:27:20.229
Not even the supervisor
or the boss can say anything.


73
00:27:22.053 --> 00:27:24.465
All day you work, so chewing tobacco

74
00:27:25.190 --> 00:27:28.069
gives you a moment to sit and breathe.

75
00:29:20.438 --> 00:29:25.114
You have to work
12 hours, no matter what.

76
00:29:26.477 --> 00:29:31.085
You work on and on and on
until the 12 hours are over.


77
00:29:34.419 --> 00:29:38.094
When I arrive at the gate for work,

78
00:29:38.189 --> 00:29:41.602
I feel like turning back right there.

79
00:29:46.364 --> 00:29:49.243
When I arrive at the gate,
my gut tells me...


80
00:29:50.435 --> 00:29:52.642
that I should just turn back.

81
00:29:52.937 --> 00:29:55.383
But it's not good to turn back.

82
00:30:14.959 --> 00:30:19.669
What you learn as a child,
you cannot learn as an adult.


83
00:30:21.232 --> 00:30:25.271
If you pay attention
to the machines when you are young,


84
00:30:25.370 --> 00:30:27.611
you become sharper as an adult.

85
00:30:28.940 --> 00:30:30.681
You become skilled.

86
00:30:30.975 --> 00:30:34.479
Whatever you learn,
you should learn as a child.


87
00:30:34.579 --> 00:30:38.322
If I learn this now,
then I can do any work later.


